Package: midifiletoolsR
Type: Package
Title: Tools to read, write, manipulate, and play MIDI files.
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Erich", "Neuwirth", , "erich.neuwirth@univie.ac.at", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Maintainer: Erich Neuwirth <erich.neuwirth@univie.ac.at>
Description: Midi files (a standard way to represent music as file) 
    are binary files and cannot be handled easily in R. 
    This toolkit allows to create midi files from dataframes
    by mapping variables to pitches, durations, volume,
    ans instruments.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.1)
Imports:
    dplyr,
    midicsvR,
    midiplayR,
    purrr,
    readr,
    rlang,
    stringr
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
